node.title: As it happened: Hurricanes stun Blues in nailbiter
node.description: The Hurricanes have claimed a 33-32 boilover win over the Blues in Super Rugby Pacific in Dunedin tonight.
node.content:
["The Hurricanes have claimed a 33-32 boilover win over the Blues in Super Rugby Pacific in Dunedin tonight.", "", "
Roger Tuivasa-Sheck looks for support during the Blues v Hurricanes, Round 2 of the Super Rugby Pacific rugby union competition at Forsyth Barr Stadium, Dunedin, New Zealand. Photo: Derek Morrison / www.photosport.nz
", "The Hurricanes captain, Ardie Savea, scored a late try to give the Wellington side the victory, after the Blues had been in the lead.", "Meanwhile, the Hurricanes suffered a 42-32 first-up loss to the Crusaders.", "RNZ's Jamie Wall was there for all the action:"]
